Metastatic cancer remains a devastating disease that threatens to disrupt entire 
family structures creating economic and psychosocial stress. Fortunately, great 
strides have resulted in improved therapies over the years but at a huge 
social-economic cost. The economic burden has risen greatly and carries with it 
new ethical concerns when deciding treatment. Here, we discuss the financial and 
ethical challenges that oncologists and their patients face in the era of novel 
treatment strategies. J. Surg. Oncol. 2016;114:323-328. © 2016 Wiley 
